import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    data.boxplot(column='precipitation', by='location', ax=ax)
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of precipitation across different locations?')
    ax.set_xlabel('Location')
    ax.set_ylabel('Precipitation')
    plt.suptitle('')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title='Location', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['temp_max'], label='Max Temperature', color='red')
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['temp_min'], label='Min Temperature', color='blue')
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Temperature')
    plt.title('How does temperature vary over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['wind'], data['temp_max'], alpha=0.5)
    plt.xlabel('Wind')
    plt.ylabel('Max Temperature')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between wind and temperature?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(['Wind vs Max Temperature'])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    weather_counts = data['weather'].value_counts()
    weather_counts.plot(kind='bar', color='c', edgecolor='k')
    
    plt.title('What is the most common weather condition across all locations?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Weather Conditions')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(['Weather Frequency'])
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
